body_text:
Thank you very much for your support 👍

Mittwoch, 24 Mai 2017, 10:55nachm. +02:00 von Lee-L-Boyd notifications@github.com<mailto:notifications@github.com>:

Hi twins14,

I am new to TF myself. What I have been doing is going over the mnist
tutorial, which is basically just classifying numbers in photos:

https://www.tensorflow.org/get_started/mnist/beginners

with the actual code you can run here:

https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/examples/tutorials/mnist/mnist.py

I have moved on to the graph visualizations tutorial here:

https://www.tensorflow.org/get_started/summaries_and_tensorboard

and code for it here:

https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/r1.1/tensorflow/examples/tutorials/mnist/mnist_with_summaries.py

I think understanding the visualization portion will be very important if
you want to actually test your code. Goodluck!


*Lee L. Boyd*
President - CSGSA at UTSA, 2017
r <lee.l.boyd@gmail.com<mailto:lee.l.boyd@gmail.com>>cx653@my.utsa.edu
(210)-404-3607
On Wed, May 24, 2017 at 3:36 PM, twins14 ***@***.******@***.***>> wrote:
 Hello Lee-L-Boyd,

 so i am twins14 and just a beginner, who is really intersting in learning
 tensorflow in my sparetime :))
 But i really need some help :((
 i am looking for a machine learning example like the "image
 classification" to reconstruct it.
 So my question to you is if you have such a code example ? 👍
 When not, do you have maybe other little examples in Tensorflow for me to
 begin learning 💯
 My email adress is: ***@***.******@***.***>

 So i would be very glad hearing from you :)

 Wish you a nice evening!

 —
